Title: Series: Theatrum Pictorium
Description: The flight into Egypt, after Domenico Fetti; with in the centre foreground of a landscape the Virgin and child riding an ass, guided by St Joseph; nearby two putti lying by the roadside. c.1656-1660 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Jan van Ossenbeeck
Intermediary draughtsman: David Teniers the Younger
Curator's comments: This is first state before number (from the first edition published in 1660), for second state see S.4591. This is one from 246 plates of Teniers' Theatre of Paintings, for comment on the series see 1850,0713.20. After the painting in the Kunsthistorisches Museum (inv. GG_155). Also see Safarik, 1990, cat. No.16.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (68)
Weigel 1843 / Suppléments au Peintre-Graveur de Adam Bartsch (307.51)
